  "prompt": "How do I change the film of a Polaroid 450 Land Camera?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to changing film in a Polaroid 450 Land Camera:\n\n1. Open the back of the camera\n- Locate the small latch or button on the side of the camera\n- Carefully open the back panel\n\n2. Remove the old film pack\n- Gently pull out the spent film pack\n- Check that the pack is completely empty\n\n3. Insert the new film pack\n- Verify you're using the correct type of film (Polaroid 100-series pack film)\n- Align the pack's contacts with the camera's electrical contacts\n- Slide the pack into place until it clicks\n\n4. Close the back of the camera\n- Ensure the back is securely closed\n- Listen for a click to confirm it's locked\n\n5. Pull out the first dark slide\n- The dark slide protects the film from light before shooting\n- Gently pull the black tab until it comes out completely\n\n6. The camera is now ready to take pictures\n- Cock the shutter/advance lever\n- Take your first shot\n\nRemember to handle the camera and film carefully, and work in a reasonably well-lit area to avoid accidentally exposing the film.",
